Boil a full #kettle{}.

When boiling, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on
high heat. Add the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%mins}.

Add the @peas{120%g} to the pan to cook for the final ~{2-3%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave
to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the pepper and stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the @British pork mince{240%g} to the pepper and cook until browned,
~{5-6%mins}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The pork
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the pork is browned, add the garlic to the pan and stir-fry for
~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{150%ml} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if
it's a little dry.

Fluff up the rice using a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the teriyaki pork stir-fry. Enjoy!